  "author": "XO_OX Designs",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "OBRIX through Aquatic Chain with Tide as the primary rhythmic feature. Wavetable source (src1Type=8) with slow scan creates a continuously evolving timbral base. Tide in Both mode (tremolo + AutoFilter simultaneously) at 0.22 Hz with sine shape creates a breathing rhythm that feels like the tidal cycle of a reef — the filter opens as the water rises, the amplitude swells, both together. Fathom Character 0.28 (slight dark). Drift 3 voices. Reef at size 0.5. The OBRIX Biophonic systems (Harmonic Field, Brick Ecology) respond to the rhythmic envelope of Tide, creating a synthesis that responds to its own spatial environment.",
